examples.en: He claimed he had been illegally detained.
The team was penalized for an illegal play.
People are tapping into the power supply illegally.
The police towed my car because it was parked illegally.
He's accused of illegally attempting to influence the jury.
Both men were found guilty of illegally entering the country.
The police impounded her car because it was illegally parked.
Courts can refuse to admit evidence obtained illegally by police.
She illegally siphoned money out of other people's bank accounts.
Millions of pounds are being salted down illegally by speculators.
They were charged with illegally diverting public funds for private use.
He was charged with illegally procuring young women for wealthy clients.
Hackers had illegally accessed information on more than 310,000 consumers.
In my mind illegally downloading a music file is coequal to stealing a CD from a store.
Authorities eventually unfettered the menagerie of wild animals that had been kept illegally as pets.
